718069f-a.title: Manhattan: Canal Street - Washington Street
718069f-a.text:
Canal Street, west from Washington to West Streets, showing a photograph taken for details of the West Street sewer project which is being constructed concurrent with the boring of the Hollland Tunnel. Work for the latter is underway on the left. This site will later become a park. Pier No. 35 is in the background. Note signs thereupon.
November 7, 1922
Standard Photographic Service
Gift of 3orough President of Manhattan
